 in Spanish. The name was imported into France in the early Middle Ages, and thence into England. It was a royal name, and its enduring popularity may have been enhanced by the fact that it was borne by a queen of England—  Isabella  (  1296–1358 ), daughter of  Philip IV  of France—even though she led a turbulent life and eventually had her husband,  Edward II , murdered."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Isabelle de Lèves was born in 1188, in Lèves, Eure-et-Loir, Centre, France. She married Guillaume d’Acquigny in 1200. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1237, at the age of 49."},"et":{"1188–1237":"1188–1237","1175–1247":"1175–1247","1210–Female":"1210–Surnud","1237":"1237","1247":"1247","1200":"1200","1188":"1188","1210":"1210","1175":"1175","Lèves, Eure-et-Loir, Centre-Val de Loire, France":"Lèves, Eure-et-Loir, Centre, Prantsusmaa","Acquigny, Eure, Normandie, France":"Acquigny, Eure, Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1188–1237":"1188–1237","1175–1247":"1175–1247","1210–Female":"1210–Kuollut","1237":"1237","1247":"1247","1200":"1200","1188":"1188","1210":"1210","1175":"1175","Lèves, Eure-et-Loir, Centre-Val de Loire, France":"Lèves, Eure-et-Loir, Centre, Ranska","Acquigny, Eure, Normandie, France":"Acquigny, Eure, Normandie, Ranska"},"fr":{"1188–1237":"1188–1237","1175–1247":"1175–1247","1210–Female":"1210–Décédée","1237":"1237","1247":"1247","1200":"1200","1188":"1188","1210":"1210","1175":"1175","Lèves, Eure-et-Loir, Centre-Val de Loire, France":"Lèves, Eure-et-Loir, Centre, France","Acquigny, Eure, Normandie, France":"Acquigny, Eure, Normandie, France","lifeSummary":"Isabelle de Lèves est née en 1188, à Lèves, Eure-et-Loir, Centre, France. Elle a épousé Guillaume d’Acquigny en 1200. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille. Elle est décédée en 1237, à l’âge de 49 ans."},"de":{"1188–1237":"1188–1237","1175–1247":"1175–1247","1210–Female":"1210–Verstorben","1237":"1237","1247":"1247","1200":"1200","1188":"1188","1210":"1210","1175":"1175","Lèves, Eure-et-Loir, Centr